During my study in my undergraduate university, I learned a lot in programming(using C++ and C#), conception of encryption and decryption, database management, operation system and process of software engineering (both appied software and system software)
Actually lots of our courses is set similar as the courses in computer science department,I do a lot of coding things and write report.

Before going to HCI field, I did quite a lot of back-end coding and programming, but I found that only efficient code can not make sure your product accepted and popular in the users' group, the interface, interaction and usability testing is also quite important, you should give users a good impression of your product and a good feeling and experience when they use your product, some great code can not be felt when users use your software or website. So with my bachelor degree in information security, I change to learn in HCI field
During my study in school of information, university of Michigan, I learned a lot of user experience research and principle of interaction design, since I have technology background, this learning give me a good understanding of how to make your code accepted and friendly to your users.
